headline: CarMax profit falls as excess inventory, falling prices squeeze margins; shares tank
summary: (Reuters) -CarMax reported a drop in second-quarter profit on Thursday, as excess inventory build up, depreciation costs and fall in used-vehicle prices hammered its margins, sending its shares tumbling down 24% in morning trade.  The used-car retailer, whose shares hit a five-year low, said its results were impacted by a pull-forward in demand earlier this year and a sharp rise in vehicle depreciation that hurt pricing power.  To offset the impact, CarMax said it cut retail margins to spur demand and deliberately slowed purchases to better align inventory with sales.

content.title: CarMax profit falls as excess inventory, falling prices squeeze margins; shares tank
content.summary: (Reuters) -CarMax reported a drop in second-quarter profit on Thursday, as excess inventory build up, depreciation costs and fall in used-vehicle prices hammered its margins, sending its shares tumbling down 24% in morning trade.  The used-car retailer, whose shares hit a five-year low, said its results were impacted by a pull-forward in demand earlier this year and a sharp rise in vehicle depreciation that hurt pricing power.  To offset the impact, CarMax said it cut retail margins to spur demand and deliberately slowed purchases to better align inventory with sales.
